column26: The prediction script inconsistently labels objects within the model’s output file, with several high-confidence predictions marked as 'unidentified.' This issue appears sporadically but impacts the accuracy of output reports. Steps to resolve: 1) Review model thresholds and update confidence level requirements for labeling. 2) Test the label mapping to confirm each predicted class aligns correctly with expected values.
